						<summary>

						<p>On the south wall, central shrine, Agastyēsvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 10: 981 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records a gift of 96 sheep for a perpetual lamp to the god Agattīśvaramuḍaiyā Mahādēvar at Tiruvānāṅgūr, a <hi rend="italic">brahmadēya</hi> in Tiruvaḷudūr-nāḍu, on the southern bank (of the river Kāvēri) by the Vēḷāṉ of Pēḻaikuḍi, a <hi rend="italic">brahmadēyam</hi> in Āmūr-nāḍu.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. XIX No. 267.</p>						

